Commentary Text: Axar to Mayank, out Hooda Run Out!! Disaster for Punjab KIngs. One of Deepak or Mayank is definitely OUT. We'll have to see the replays to ascertain who is actually out. Both were running to the same end, both are short, but it's Hooda whose bat is in front of Mayank. So, it should be him who should be walking back to the pavilion. Yes, Hooda is OUT. Confusion and more confusion in the running between the wickets, helter-skelter running and the Kings are losing the plot. Mayank punched one to the right of Hetmyer and started off for a quick single, Hooda was ball watching, he did start, but then stopped to see if Hetmyer had stopped the ball on the dive. He did and so did Hooda, who was now running back, Mayank kept running, but was well behind his partner when Axar tipped the bails off. To be on the safer side, Axar also lobbed the ball towards the keeper. Run-out at both ends, but Hooda's the man who has to depart. Hooda run out (Hetmyer/Axar) 1(1)

Commentary Text: Axar to Malan, out Bowled!! That's the end of Malan - played far too many dot balls, the pressure was on him and in looking to target Axar, he ends up losing his leg-stump. Nicely bowled though - slowed down the pace and got this one to slide into the left-hander, Malan was looking to hoist it over mid-wicket, was through with the shot far too early and then turns back to watch his leg-stump on the ground. Malan b Axar 26(26) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Axar to Malan, leg byes, 1 run, big appeal for lbw, struck down! Delhi have challenged the decision. 96.1kph, quick in-turner from over the wicket and Malan shuffled across a long way before missing the glance. Fair delivery. No inside edge, the same has been confirmed by the UltraEdge. Over to ball-tracking: clipping leg and it's umpire's call. That was a good shout from Delhi, Malan lucky to get away with it. A sigh of relief for the No. 1 T20I batter

Commentary Text: Rabada to Gayle, out Bowled!! Rabada wins the battle against Gayle! A full toss at 143.4kph, Gayle didn't see that coming. Meant to be the yorker and Rabada missed it by a long way - was a high full toss. Gayle was probably expecting a short one. Backed away to hurriedly tap it into the off-side and completely got beaten on the outside edge. The ball makes a mess of the sticks! A distraught Gayle walks back. Wasn't a happy sight for the batter. Missed the ball completely and the back leg was off air with the off-stump cartwheeling... Gayle b Rabada 13(9) [4s-1 6s-1]
